Detailed Description

Crash log host architecture information.

Provides host architecture information such as the model name, processor type, and logical and hardware processor counts.

Member Function Documentation

- (id) initWithModelName: (NSString *)  modelName
processorInfo: (PLCrashReportProcessorInfo *)  processorInfo
processorCount: (NSUInteger)  processorCount
logicalProcessorCount: (NSUInteger)  logicalProcessorCount 

Initialize a new machine info data object.

Parameters:
modelNameThe hardware model name (eg, MacBookPro6,1). This may be nil.
processorInfoThe processor type.
processorCountThe number of actual physical processor cores. Note that the number of active processors may be managed by the operating system's power management system, and this value may not reflect the number of active processors at the time of the crash.
logicalProcessorCountThe number of logical processors. Note that the number of active processors may be managed by the operating system's power management system, and this value may not reflect the number of active processors at the time of the crash.
